## SPL injection — all edge cases

### Strategy detection order (matters — check in this order)
1. `| inputlookup` → return SPL unchanged, skip indexing
2. `| tstats` → return SPL unchanged, add warning
3. `| lookup <word>` → lookup strategy
4. `index=` in outer query → standard strategy
5. nothing found → no_index strategy (prepend)

### Only replace OUTER index= — never inside subsearch brackets
```python
bracket_pos = spl.find('[')
outer = spl[:bracket_pos] if bracket_pos != -1 else spl
inner = spl[bracket_pos:] if bracket_pos != -1 else ''
result = _replace_index(outer, run_id) + inner
```

### Replace the full rowIdentifier string first
`input.row_identifier` may be `"index=main sourcetype=firewall"` — replace the entire string, not just `index=`.
Try exact string match first. Fall back to regex `index=\w+` only if exact match fails.

### `| search index=x` mid-pipeline — replace only pre-pipe
```python
first_pipe = spl.find('|')
if first_pipe > 0 and re.search(r'\bindex\s*=', spl[:first_pipe], re.IGNORECASE):
    pre  = INDEX_PATTERN.sub(replacement, spl[:first_pipe], count=1)
    return pre + spl[first_pipe:]
return INDEX_PATTERN.sub(replacement, spl, count=1)
```

### `| tstats` — do not inject
Return SPL unchanged. Add warning: `"tstats queries cannot be injected with test data. Use testType='query_only'."`

### no_index — prepend
`index=temp_query_tester run_id=<run_id> ` prepended to start of SPL.

