## makeresults data indexing — no single quotes ever

Single quotes in Splunk SPL eval break silently. Always embed event data as JSON:

```python
# CORRECT
json_str = json.dumps(events, ensure_ascii=False)
json_str = json_str.replace('\\', '\\\\').replace('"', '\\"')
spl = f'| makeresults count=1 | eval _raw="{json_str}" | spath | mvexpand _raw | collect index=temp_query_tester sourcetype=query_tester_input'

# WRONG — breaks if any value contains a single quote or apostrophe
spl = f"| eval host='{value}'"
```

Batch in groups of 1000 events per `collect` call.

