## Payload parsing — camelCase to snake_case mapping

Frontend sends camelCase. Parse to snake_case dataclasses. Key renames:

```
testName          -> test_name
testType          -> test_type
rowIdentifier     -> row_identifier
generatorConfig   -> generator_config
eventCount        -> event_count
fieldName         -> field_name
generationType    -> generation_type
validationType    -> validation_type
fieldConditions   -> field_conditions
fieldLogic        -> field_logic
validationScope   -> validation_scope
resultCount       -> result_count
operator          -> condition      <- RENAMED (frontend "operator" = backend "condition")
scenarioScope     -> scenario_scope
```

Normalization — handle before building dataclasses:
- `scenarios` absent or null → empty list (query_only)
- `generatorConfig` null → disabled generator
- `validation.fieldConditions` null → no field conditions
- `validation.resultCount` null → skip count check
- `input.events` is `[]` or `[{}]` → skip indexing

