## Response keys — exact camelCase, never renamed

Frontend TypeScript reads these exact keys. Do not use `dataclasses.asdict()` — it produces snake_case.
Write explicit `_to_dict()` helpers.

```
status, message, timestamp, testName, testType,
totalScenarios, passedScenarios, warnings,
splAnalysis.unauthorizedCommands, splAnalysis.unusualCommands,
splAnalysis.uniqLimitations, splAnalysis.commandsUsed,
scenarioResults[].scenarioName, .passed, .executionTimeMs,
.resultCount, .injectedSpl, .error,
.validations[].field, .condition, .expected, .actual, .passed, .message
```

Status logic: `success` = all passed, `partial` = some passed, `error` = none passed.

