## Dataclass conventions

```python
@dataclass
class ScenarioResult:
    """Result of running one scenario."""
    scenario_name: str                                   # required fields first
    passed: bool
    execution_time_ms: int
    result_count: int
    injected_spl: str
    validations: List[ValidationDetail] = field(default_factory=list)
    error: Optional[str] = None                          # optional fields with defaults last
```

- One dataclass per concept — no plain dicts between modules
- `List[X]` fields use `field(default_factory=list)`, not `= None`
- `Optional[X]` fields default to `None`

